sentences: Coco Montoya (born Henry Montoya, October 2, 1951, Santa Monica, California) is an American blues guitarist and singer and former member of John Mayall & the Bluesbreakers.
In 1995 he appeared with the Cate Brothers for the resumption of their recording career on their release, Radioland.
In 2002, he featured on the Bo Diddley tribute album Hey Bo Diddley â€“ A Tribute!, performing the song "Pills."
His 2019 recording, Coming In Hot, was chosen as a 'Favorite Blues Album' by AllMusic.
Montoya and his longtime girlfriend Lenora married in 2009.
He has two daughters; Jasmin (born 1980) and Donna (born 1988).

In the early 1980s John Mayall heard Montoya playing guitar in a Los Angeles bar.
Montoya's career began in the mid 1970s when Albert Collins asked him to join his band as drummer.
He remained a member of the band for 10 years.
Since that same year, Montoya has recorded several solo albums.
